comment.commentLine: Note: for VM's UEK2 and UEK4 can not be mixed.
Dom0 needs to be equal or higher than DomU.
Note: As part of the deployment,
Oracle always installs the latest Exadata Storage software.
This means that different machines could have different versions of
the Storage software even if they are deployed around the same time.
An example of the difference between machines would be the Kernel
version that is installed. Please review the Exadata Storage
software version to be deployed with the Engineer during the
planning phase of the deployment.
Generic Questions:
Q1: For compute and storage nodes, please indicate desired OS image.
Q2: For internal Cisco switch,
will Spanning Tree Protocol need to be disabled due to BPDU Guard?
Compute Node Questions:
Q3: For 10G/25G Optical cables, do you have existing certified SFP Modules?
Q4: For LACP, will you use default bond options?
If not, please specify desired bond options.
Q5: For DR machines,
have you ensured the RDBMS version matches the production version?
Q6: For User Security with LDAP Servers,
have you confirmed the UID/GID's are matching your LDAP servers?
Expansion Questions:
Q7: What other/existing engineered system will
this machine/these parts be connected to via InfiniBand?
Q8: Have you ensured that the InfiniBand IPs do not overlap and
that they are in the proper subnet?
Q9: Is an InfiniBand Listener needed for SQL communication
on the InfiniBand fabric?
Q10: Have you ensured that the private IB subnet does not overlap the
client, mgmt, and backup networks?
Q11: For storage expansion, should the ASM diskgroups be extended,
new diskgroups created, or both?
Q12: For PXE imaging, can the Internal Cisco uplink port be unplugged,
or do we need an isolated switch?
Additional Comments:
